      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "bf3177bf91361bd7",
      "text": "But one thing the re-readers can't do is ask questions. We wonder if listeners of the time could. The dense, concentrated text speaks against it. The master himself has asked enough questions, for example, where is the Zettel (note) that says that all the other fifty or sixty thousand Zettel (notes) are wrong."
